OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780391237
OL,3,CMan who murdered student with Sikh
OL,4,Cceremonial knife jailed for life
OL,6,FDigwa, who must serve at least 21
OL,7,Fyears in prison, told police that Mr
OL,8,FNowak, who he described as drunk, had
OL,9,Fracially abused him before punching
OL,10,Fhim and knocking his turban off.
OL,12,FHe said he had stabbed Mr Nowak to the
OL,13,Fback of his legs in self-defence after
OL,14,FMr Nowak had threatened him and
OL,15,Fgrabbed him by the hair, but said he
OL,16,Fhad not realised at the time he had
OL,17,Fcaused the fatal stab wound to his
OL,18,Fchest.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780391237
OL,3,CMan who murdered student with Sikh
OL,4,Cceremonial knife jailed for life
OL,6,FBut during the trial, the prosecution
OL,7,Fsaid Digwa had "lied" and deceived
OL,8,Fofficers who attended the scene by
OL,9,Fclaiming that he had not stabbed Mr
OL,10,FNowak despite the student's pleas for
OL,11,Fhelp.
OL,13,FThat led officers to arrest Mr Nowak
OL,14,Fand place him in handcuffs moments
OL,15,Fbefore he collapsed and became
OL,16,Funconscious.
OL,18,FHe died despite their best efforts to
OL,19,Fgive him first aid.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780391237
OL,3,CMan who murdered student with Sikh
OL,4,Cceremonial knife jailed for life
OL,6,FAt the sentencing hearing at
OL,7,FSouthampton Crown Court today (1
OL,8,FJune), Nicholas Lobbenberg KC,
OL,9,Fprosecuting, said: "This was a
OL,10,Fsustained attack on an unarmed man.
OL,11,FThe defendant is skilled with weapons,
OL,12,Fhe trained with weapons, he sleeps in
OL,13,Fa room with weapons, he searches for
OL,14,Fweapons on his phone.
OL,16,F"The Crown says he is a man with a
OL,17,Fweapons obsession. He chose to use a
OL,18,Fweapon on the streets of Southampton,
OL,19,Fthis demonstrates in his mind what he
OL,20,Fhad was a weapon ready and available
OL,21,Ffor his use."
OL,26,@qD@TOUxD@AOU}D@MO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780391237
OL,3,CMan who murdered student with Sikh
OL,4,Cceremonial knife jailed for life
OL,6,F"Henry Nowak dying alone, humiliated
OL,7,Fand handcuffed was a direct
OL,8,Fconsequence of Vickrum Digwa's
OL,9,Fdishonesty.
OL,11,F"Vickrum Digwa chose on two occasions
OL,12,Fto make videos, first of Henry fleeing
OL,13,Fand then of Henry dying with close-ups
OL,14,Fof his face. The Crown says that is
OL,15,Fboth intrusive and humiliating.
OL,17,F"His defence describing Henry as a
OL,18,Fviolent drunk racist aggressor
OL,19,Fcompounds the grief of the family."
OL,26,@sD@AOUyD@AOU{D@cO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780391237
OL,3,CMan who murdered student with Sikh
OL,4,Cceremonial knife jailed for life
OL,6,FLucy, the mother of Henry, said in a
OL,7,Fstatement read to the court: "Henry
OL,8,Fwas ambitious, determined and full of
OL,9,Flife, he was a messy sod and always
OL,10,Fhungry, but he had his whole life
OL,11,Fahead of him, that future has been
OL,12,Fcruelly taken away.
OL,14,F"The impact of his loss has been
OL,15,Fdevastating not only for me but for
OL,16,Four entire family and for all who knew
OL,17,Fhim, we are learning to support one
OL,18,Fanother through this unimaginable
OL,19,Fgrief, but the pain is constant, our
OL,20,Ffamily will never be the same.
OL,26,@oD@^OUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780391237
OL,3,CMan who murdered student with Sikh
OL,4,Cceremonial knife jailed for life
OL,6,F"He will never be forgotten and he
OL,7,Fwill always be loved beyond words. No
OL,8,Fsentence handed down will bring Henry
OL,9,Fback."
OL,11,FShe also described the moment her son
OL,12,Ftold her, his face "beaming", that he
OL,13,Fhad been an offered a place to study
OL,14,Fat the University of Southampton while
OL,15,Fon holiday in Greece, adding: "It was
OL,16,Fone of the proudest moments of my life
OL,17,Fand a moment I will treasure forever."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@FO]tD@TOUtD@\O]wD@_OUyD@fO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1780391237
OL,3,CMan who murdered student with Sikh
OL,4,Cceremonial knife jailed for life
OL,6,FOlivia, Henry's sister, spoke directly
OL,7,Fto the defendant as she told him: "If
OL,8,Fyou had known him, you would never
OL,9,Fhave hurt him."
OL,11,FShe told the court: "My brother was my
OL,12,Ffirst best friend, an unbreakable
OL,13,Fbond, we lived our life to the fullest
OL,14,Ftogether."
OL,16,FShe added: "He lit up every room that
OL,17,Fhe walked into and the world became
OL,18,Fless valuable the day he left."
OL,26,@oD@cOUqD@OO]sD@UOUvD@JO]xD@LOUzD@_O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/9
